* Wed Nov 07 2018 Scott Armiger <scott.armiger@onyxpoint.com> - 1.1.0-0
- Fixed a bug in params.pp where it was attempting to configure ldap
  variables even when $ldap was set to false.
- Updated to use data in modules when applicable, and remove params.pp
- No longer support Puppet less than 4.10.4
- Minor changes
  - Convert README to markdown and add a REFERENCE.md
  - Hashes in Puppet language should have keys that are quoted strings
  - Updated acceptance test
  - Support puppetlabs/stdlib 6.0.0
- New LDAP configuation method
  - If providing LDAP configuration via $ldap_cfg, SIMP's smart defaults
    will not be used. The defaults will also not be used if $ldap or
    `simp_options::ldap` is false. Make sure all needed options are set if
    specifying a custom $ldap_cfg.
  - New parameters, to take advantage of data in modules
    - $default_cfg
    - $simp_ldap_conf
    - $ldap
    - $base_dn
    - $bind_dn
    - $bind_pw
    - $ldap_urls
    - $admin_pw
    - $ldap_verbose_logging

* Mon Oct 29 2018 Liz Nemsick <lnemsick.simp@gmail.com> - 1.1.0-0
- Fix bug in resource ordering of pki::copy and grafana::service
- Use simplib::passgen() in lieu of deprecated passgen()
- Update badges and contribution guide URL in README.md

* Tue Sep 11 2018 Nicholas Markowski <nicholas.markowski@onyxpoint.com> - 1.1.0-0
